<item>
            <title>[LU-15532] OOM in osd_device_alloc()</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15532</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;With my debug kernel (3.10.0-1062.9.1.el7.x86_64.debug) and v2_14_57-74-g5cde554f7f, &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;struct brw_stats&lt;/tt&gt; is now 47KB and the ldiskfs &lt;tt&gt;struct osd_device&lt;/tt&gt; 50KB.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In &lt;tt&gt;osd_device_alloc()&lt;/tt&gt; we allocate the device using &lt;tt&gt;OBD_ALLOC_PTR()&lt;/tt&gt; so this is an order 4 kmalloc which OOM pretty easily.&lt;/p&gt;


</description>
